    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Interesting. I've heard some legal scholars argue that substantive due process is actually dangerous because it gives judges too much power to make up new rights that aren't explicitly written in the Constitution. They say it undermines the democratic process. How would you respond to the idea that this doctrine is actually an undemocratic overreach by the courts?",
